oc:kn_20195d08 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any multi-email drip sequence (welcome, onboarding, nurture)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure automated sequences with progressive goals: welcome → educate → engage → social proof → convert → urgency, spacing emails 2-4 days apart." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Progressive sequencing builds trust incrementally and mirrors the buyer's journey, resulting in higher conversion rates than ad-hoc email timing." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_326a9407 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before launching campaigns on a new or cold domain" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ensure SPF, DKIM, and DMARC authentication are configured before sending campaigns. Warm up new sending domains over 2-4 weeks with gradual volume increases of max 20% per week." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skipping authentication or sending high volume from unwarmed domains causes inbox providers to reject or bulk-folder emails, destroying deliverability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_438238e1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating email campaign performance" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Healthy email campaign benchmarks: open rate 20-25%, click rate 2-5%, conversion rate 1-3%, unsubscribe rate <0.5%, bounce rate <2%, spam complaints <0.1%." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These industry benchmarks provide objective thresholds to diagnose whether campaigns are underperforming on delivery, content, or list health." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_44546395 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When optimizing email campaign performance" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A/B test high-impact elements first (subject lines, send time, CTA buttons) with 2-3 variants on 20% of the list before sending to the full audience." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Subject lines and send time have the highest impact on open and click rates; testing low-impact elements like fonts wastes sample size and time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_48430bb2 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring any automated email sequence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Automated sequences should have clear exit conditions (upgrade, unsubscribe, purchase completion) to prevent sending irrelevant follow-up emails to converted subscribers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without exit conditions, converted subscribers receive inappropriate nurture or promotional emails, causing frustration and increasing unsubscribe rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8454aac4 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining target audiences for campaigns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Segment lists by behavioral signals (engagement level, purchase history, product interest) rather than just demographics to improve relevance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Behavioral segments (opened 5 of last 5 vs. no opens in 30 days) predict responsiveness far better than demographic data alone, improving click and conversion rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e3dbcdd7 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before sending any email campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify all emails include a prominent unsubscribe link and physical mailing address (CAN-SPAM requirement) before sending any campaign." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing unsubscribe links or physical addresses violate CAN-SPAM regulations and increase spam complaints, risking legal liability and sender reputation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_edec6c6b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any email marketing content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid spam trigger words (free, act now, limited time, click here) in email copy and maintain a 60:40 text-to-image ratio to stay out of spam folders." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Spam filters penalize emails with high spam-word density and poor text-to-image balance, directly harming deliverability and open rates." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

